y CT angiography. <em>AJR Am J Roentgenol</em> 2011;196(4):801–806.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/AJR.10.5786">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21427328/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=A+prospective+randomized+controlled+trial+to+assess+the+diagnostic+performance+of+reduced+tube+voltage+for+coronary+CT+angiography&amp;author=J+Leipsic&amp;author=TM+LaBounty&amp;author=GB+Mancini&amp;publication_year=2011&amp;journal=AJR+Am+J+Roentgenol&amp;pages=801-806&amp;doi=10.2214%2FAJR.10.5786&amp;pmid=21427328">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">8.</div><div id="r8" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Yildiz A, Okcun B, Peker T, Arslan C, Olcay A, Bulent Vatan M. Prevalence of coronary artery anomalies in 12,457 adult patients who underwent coronary angiography. <em>Clin Cardiol</em> 2010;33(12): E60–E64.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/clc.20588">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21184546/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Prevalence+of+coronary+artery+anomalies+in+12%2C457+adult+patients+who+underwent+coronary+angiography&amp;author=A+Yildiz&amp;author=B+Okcun&amp;author=T+Peker&amp;author=C+Arslan&amp;author=A+Olcay&amp;author=M+Bulent+Vatan&amp;publication_year=2010&amp;journal=Clin+Cardiol&amp;pages=E60-E64&amp;doi=10.1002%2Fclc.20588&amp;pmid=21184546">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">9.</div><div id="r9" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Peña E, Nguyen ET, Me